Intermediate Split

For consistent gym-goers ready for more targeted training

This 4-day upper/lower split allows for better volume and recovery for each muscle group. It's ideal for those who have mastered the basic movements and are ready for more targeted training.

Day 1: Upper Body

  • Bench Press: 4 sets x 8 reps
  • Bent Over Rows: 4 sets x 10 reps
  • Overhead Press: 3 sets x 10 reps
  • Pull-ups/Lat Pulldowns: 3 sets x 10 reps
  • Tricep Pushdowns: 3 sets x 12 reps
  • Bicep Curls: 3 sets x 12 reps

Day 2: Lower Body

  • Squats: 4 sets x 8 reps
  • Romanian Deadlifts: 4 sets x 10 reps
  • Leg Press: 3 sets x 12 reps
  • Leg Curls: 3 sets x 12 reps
  • Calf Raises: 4 sets x 15 reps
  • Planks: 3 sets x 45 seconds

Day 3: Rest

Active recovery day. Light cardio or mobility work recommended.

Day 4: Upper Body

  • Incline Bench Press: 4 sets x 8 reps
  • Cable Rows: 4 sets x 10 reps
  • Lateral Raises: 3 sets x 12 reps
  • Face Pulls: 3 sets x 15 reps
  • Skull Crushers: 3 sets x 12 reps
  • Hammer Curls: 3 sets x 12 reps

Day 5: Lower Body

  • Deadlifts: 4 sets x 6 reps
  • Front Squats: 3 sets x 8 reps
  • Walking Lunges: 3 sets x 10 reps/leg
  • Leg Extensions: 3 sets x 12 reps
  • Seated Calf Raises: 4 sets x 15 reps
  • Russian Twists: 3 sets x 20 reps

Days 6-7: Rest

Weekend recovery. Focus on nutrition and rest, with optional light activity.
